description:
File: python/src/lichen/link/link_layer.py:551-554, 485-494

When receiving our own frame (loopback), _find_sender returns a PeerIdentity from our pubkey:

    if verify(self.identity.pubkey, signable, signature):
        return PeerIdentity.from_pubkey(self.identity.pubkey)

Then replay_protector uses this pubkey:

    if not self.replay_protector.check_and_update(
        sender.pubkey, frame.epoch, frame.seqnum
    ):

This creates a ReplayWindow for our own pubkey. The first loopback frame is accepted. This is likely intentional (to process the first occurrence), but has implications:

1. Our TX sequence and the loopback RX window can diverge
2. If we send seq 100, receive it as loopback, then send seq 99 (due to a bug), our own frame at seq 99 would be rejected as replay

This may be correct behavior, but the interaction is subtle and undocumented.
